main event: A bright silver fast-moving object was reported near Aztec, New Mexico on 25 June 1966.
interesting points: The sighting was reported by one civilian witness., The observation lasted for a very short time., The object was described as silvery and moving rapidly., The object was believed to have fallen on or near Mt. Lebo, near Cedar Hill, New Mexico., A preliminary analysis suggested that the object was likely a bright meteor.
